# davidhoang-web - Cursor Agent Rules

## Project Overview

Personal website for davidhoang.com built with Astro. Features blog posts, career odyssey, design resources, and experimental UI components.

## Repository Info

- **GitHub**: `davidhoang/davidhoang-web`
- **Jira Project**: **PC** (Personal/Portfolio/Content)
- **Default Branch**: `main`
- **Framework**: Astro with TypeScript, React components

## Jira Integration

### Project Mapping
- **Jira Key**: PC (e.g., PC-25, PC-26)
- **Repository**: This repo (`davidhoang/davidhoang-web`)
- **Branch Format**: `cursor/PC-{number}-{description}`

### When Working on PC Issues
1. Verify you have this repo (`davidhoang-web`) open in Cursor
2. Check the Jira issue details before starting
3. Create branches following: `cursor/PC-XXX-short-description`
4. Link commits to Jira: `PC-XXX: Commit message`

### Example Jira Issues
- `PC-25`: Implement comments system for blog posts
- `PC-XX`: Add new blog features, UI improvements, content updates

## Core Principles

1. **Astro-First**: Use Astro components (.astro) by default
2. **React for Interactivity**: Use React/TSX only when client-side interactivity needed
3. **Performance**: Optimize images, fonts, lazy-load where possible
4. **Accessibility**: Maintain semantic HTML, ARIA labels, keyboard navigation
5. **Design System**: Follow existing CSS modules and themes

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Astro 4.x
- **Styling**: CSS Modules + Global CSS
- **Components**: Astro components + React (for interactive UI)
- **TypeScript**: Strict mode enabled
- **Content**: Markdown + MDX for blog posts
- **Deployment**: Vercel
- **Fonts**: Self-hosted (see public/fonts/)

## Development Commands

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Development server (port 4321)
npm run dev

# Build for production
npm run build

# Preview production build
npm run preview

# Type checking
npm run astro check
```

## Project Structure

```
davidhoang-web/
├── src/
│   ├── components/         # Astro & React components
│   │   ├── *.astro        # Server-side components
│   │   └── *.tsx          # Client-side React components
│   ├── content/           # Content collections
│   │   ├── writing/       # Blog posts (MDX)
│   │   └── notes/         # Quick notes (MDX)
│   ├── layouts/           # Page layouts
│   ├── pages/             # Routes (file-based routing)
│   ├── styles/            # CSS modules & global styles
│   └── utils/             # Helper functions
├── public/                # Static assets
│   ├── images/           # Images
│   └── fonts/            # Self-hosted fonts
└── scripts/               # Build & utility scripts
```

## Key Files

- `astro.config.mjs` - Astro configuration
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration
- `src/content/config.ts` - Content collections schema
- `src/layouts/BlogPost.astro` - Blog post layout template
- `src/components/CommentsSection.astro` - Comments component (stub for PC-25)

## Code Patterns

### Creating Astro Components

```astro
---
// Component script (runs on server)
interface Props {
  title: string;
  description?: string;
}

const { title, description } = Astro.props;
---

<div class="component">
  <h2>{title}</h2>
  {description && <p>{description}</p>}
</div>

<style>
  .component {
    /* Scoped styles */
  }
</style>
```

### Adding React Components (Client-Side)

```tsx
// src/components/InteractiveWidget.tsx
import { useState } from 'react';

export default function InteractiveWidget() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
  
  return (
    <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>
      Clicked {count} times
    </button>
  );
}

// Use in .astro file:
// <InteractiveWidget client:load />
```

### Adding Blog Posts

Create `src/content/writing/post-slug.mdx`:

```mdx
---
title: "Post Title"
publishDate: "2026-05-22"
description: "Brief description"
tags: ["design", "tech"]
---

Post content here...
```

## Current Work: PC-25 (Comments System)

**Issue**: Implement comments system for blog posts
**Component**: `src/components/CommentsSection.astro` (currently a stub)
**Layout**: `src/layouts/BlogPost.astro` (includes CommentsSection)

### Options to Consider
1. **Giscus** (GitHub Discussions) - No backend, free, privacy-friendly
2. **Utterances** (GitHub Issues) - Simpler than Giscus
3. **Custom** (Supabase/Firebase) - More control, requires backend

### Implementation Checklist
- [ ] Choose comments provider
- [ ] Update `CommentsSection.astro` with integration code
- [ ] Add necessary scripts/imports
- [ ] Style to match site design
- [ ] Test on sample blog post
- [ ] Update documentation

## Styling Guidelines

### CSS Architecture
- **Global styles**: `src/styles/global.css`
- **Reset**: `src/styles/reset.css`
- **Modules**: `src/styles/modules/*.css`
- **Component styles**: Scoped `<style>` in .astro files

### Design System Variables

```css
/* Colors */
--color-text: /* Dynamic based on theme */
--color-bg: /* Dynamic based on theme */
--color-accent: /* Theme-specific */

/* Typography */
--font-body: /* Variable font */
--font-heading: /* Variable font */

/* Spacing */
--space-xs: 0.5rem;
--space-sm: 1rem;
--space-md: 2rem;
--space-lg: 4rem;
```

### Responsive Breakpoints

```css
/* Mobile first approach */
@media (min-width: 640px) { /* sm */ }
@media (min-width: 768px) { /* md */ }
@media (min-width: 1024px) { /* lg */ }
@media (min-width: 1280px) { /* xl */ }
```

## Themes System

The site has a dynamic theming system:
- Multiple color themes (check `src/data/daily-themes.json`)
- Font pairings that change with themes
- Shader backgrounds and effects
- Theme persistence in localStorage

## Content Collections

### Writing (Blog Posts)

Schema includes:
- `title`: Post title
- `publishDate`: ISO date string
- `description`: SEO description
- `tags`: Array of tags
- `isDraft`: Boolean (drafts not shown in production)
- `ogImage`: Optional social image

### Notes (Quick Thoughts)

Shorter content pieces with stages:
- `seedling`: New idea
- `budding`: Developing
- `evergreen`: Mature content

## Image Optimization

```astro
---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import myImage from '../assets/my-image.jpg';
---

<Image 
  src={myImage} 
  alt="Description" 
  width={800}
  height={600}
  loading="lazy"
/>
```

## Site Navigation

Navigation is split between the **top nav** (primary pages) and the **footer** (secondary / long-tail pages).

### Top nav (`src/data/navigation.ts` → `navItems`)
- About, Writing, Featured, Subscribe
- Rendered in `src/components/Navigation.astro`
- Keep this list short — do **not** add Notes or Advising here

### Footer only (`src/components/Footer.astro`)
- **Notes** and **Advising** live in the footer, not the top nav
- Practice column: About, Advising, Career Odyssey, etc.
- Writing column: Writing, Notes, Now, RSS feeds, etc.
- Add secondary or niche pages here rather than cluttering the top nav

### Command palette (`commandPalettePages` in `src/data/navigation.ts`)
- Includes all discoverable pages (Notes, Advising, Now, Career Odyssey, etc.)
- Individual notes and writing posts are indexed at build time in `Navigation.astro`

When adding a new page, decide: primary destination → `navItems`; secondary → footer links in `Footer.astro`; always add to `commandPalettePages` if users should find it via ⌘K search.

## Common Tasks

### Adding a New Page

1. Create `src/pages/new-page.astro`
2. Use existing layout: `import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro'`
3. Add to top nav (`navItems`), footer (`Footer.astro`), and/or command palette (`commandPalettePages`) as appropriate — see **Site Navigation** above

### Adding a New Component

1. Decide: Astro (.astro) or React (.tsx)?
2. Create in `src/components/`
3. Export if needed
4. Import where used
5. Add styles (scoped or module)

### Working with Blog Posts

```bash
# Create new post
touch src/content/writing/my-new-post.mdx

# Add frontmatter and content
# Post automatically appears at /writing/my-new-post
```

### Adding Third-Party Scripts

For external integrations (analytics, comments):

```astro
---
// In <head> or before </body>
---
<script is:inline src="https://example.com/script.js"></script>

<!-- Or load client-side -->
<script>
  // Client-side JS here
</script>
```

## Testing & Quality

### Before Committing
```bash
# Type check
npm run astro check

# Build test
npm run build

# Preview
npm run preview
```

### Performance Checklist
- [ ] Images optimized (WebP format preferred)
- [ ] Fonts subset and preloaded
- [ ] Scripts loaded with appropriate strategy
- [ ] CSS minimized and scoped
- [ ] No layout shift (CLS)

## Deployment

- **Platform**: Vercel
- **Auto-deploy**: Pushes to `main` branch
- **Preview**: PRs get preview URLs
- **Build command**: `npm run build`
- **Output**: `dist/`

## Security & Best Practices

- ✅ No API keys in client-side code
- ✅ Environment variables for secrets (if needed)
- ✅ Validate external data/content
- ✅ Sanitize user input (if accepting any)
- ✅ Use Content Security Policy headers

## Cursor Agent Guidelines

When working on this repo as a Cursor agent:

1. **Read existing patterns** before implementing new features
2. **Maintain consistency** with existing components and styles
3. **Optimize for performance** (this is a portfolio site)
4. **Test responsiveness** on mobile, tablet, desktop
5. **Preserve accessibility** features
6. **Update related docs** when changing architecture
7. **Link work to PC-XXX** Jira issues in commits

### For PC-25 Specifically (Comments)

1. Research Giscus/Utterances integration with Astro
2. Update `CommentsSection.astro` component
3. Test on a real blog post (e.g., `/writing/some-post`)
4. Ensure theme compatibility
5. Verify mobile responsiveness
6. Check accessibility (keyboard navigation, screen readers)
7. Update this doc with implementation notes

